  "description": "Here’s a photo y’all may have seen in your history books, but maybe not. It comes up a lot in materials covering the relationship between Kyriarchists colonizing Turtle Island and the Lakota:\nThis is a photograph taken in 1892. It shows pile of buffalo skulls, demonstrating a “successful” buffalo hunt, by colonizer standards. You see, their goal wasn’t to provide food for their communities, but to remove my people’s food supply. It was a mechanism of colonial genocide, that just happened to use the extinction of another species.\n",
